<br>
[quote] you cant talk to dead people!! (well...not in EQ anyway) [/quote]<br>
<br>
First - If you put limitations saying that above statement is true, then your expecting everyone else to RP your way. Thats just not fair. Whos to say you cant talk to dead people here? /boggle<br>
<br>
A good friend of mine, took me to see a picture of his father in the 3rd gate of Neriak. As we sat there, with one lady in attendance with us (his mate now that i think about it) , we 'felt' his fathers spirit in the painting. I remember sitting there thinking that my friend was going to become possesed or something and attack me, for he was acting so strangly. (least I RPed it like that) The lady with us, pleaded with us to leave she was so taken back. Next chapter in their story had his lady giving birth to a child, who actually was his father reborn ICly(though played by a different person in RL)<br>
<br>
Second - I myself rerolled from Imasu the rogue to a cleric named Corrino then back to Imasu the rogue once more. All RP, and ive a storyline written, detailing my adventures. Did Corrino know people from Imasu's past, of course he did, because he IS the same character! Do I RP like I know Corino's past even though I rerolled him? Of course I do. They ARE the same character.<br>
<br>
Thirdly - Where in the hell do people (aimed at no one in particular, because sooo many people do it) come off saying that people dont know how to RP 'properly' /boggle some more<br>
<br>
Another friend of mine, RPed that he was a kid from NY that got jumped by a gang of people (his RL friends). Pushed out into the street where he got hit by a car or something, and awoke in Norrath. He walked around for awhile in Qeynos asking people where in the hell he was, for like 4 hours. Flipping out when people came up to him with swords raised and all, yelling that he 'just wanted to find his way back home' as he ran for his life.<br>
<br>
Afew people asked em what calss he was, and he would respond 'middle class I guess, though I dont have a penny to my name right now, so I guess im poor now' That got afew strange looks to be sure. People would ask him what profession he was, trying to RP with em, to which he would reply 'Well, I helped put up the stage in central park recently with a construction crew, you know the one with the big clock?'<br>
<br>
People where like 'hey! I know that place!' People ate it up. They thought it was hilarious. Something like Lost in Time, or whatever that old show was.<br>
<br>
Ohh sorry, thats not RP, cause hes playing RL in a game...<br>
<br>
Let me just point out that he played his character as though his origins were seperate from the environment in which he was cast (as opposed to - being of the environment and RPing to the environment as though it were normal. Cause for his character, it was anything but normal!), so maybe thats a no no in the big book of do's and don't you're coming out with (hopefully soon so us non-tabletop players can conform).<br>
<br>
Anyhow....those first two are examples of how a 'dead' character can still be felt and intereacted with. All in RP, mind you.<br>
<br>
The third one was aimed at anyone that has a control problem, when it comes to other peoples RP.<br>
<br>
Bottom line is. Get over yourselves (you people who NEED to control others RP)<br>
<br>
/hijack off<br>
<br>
From what I read you saying she said to you. I personally see/would have saw, a golden opportunity to RP with her. Not as whoever she thought you were, but you could have viewed her as an delusional person ICly, and whatnot (which I do believe you tryed to at first). Maybe blind, far-sighted perhaps, and not really knowing who you were...so many ways to RP that situation there.<br>
